<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12214k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12214k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12214k"> 214(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> exporting SS</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les vampires, tant&ocirc;t dangereux et m&eacute;chants, tant&ocirc;t bienfaisants et malheureux, sont des morts qui ne sont pas morts tout &agrave; fait; leur corps n&apos;a pas pu se d&eacute;composer comme il faut, soit que les rites fun&eacute;raires n&apos;aient pas &eacute;t&eacute; compl&egrave;tement ex&eacute;cut&eacute;s &agrave; leur &eacute;gard, soit qu&apos;ils aient manqu&eacute; leur effet; leur &acirc;me n&apos;a pas quitt&eacute; leur corps. <br><font color="green">[Vampires, sometimes dangerous and bad, sometimes benevolent and unhappy, are dead people who are not quite dead; their bodies have not properly decomposed, either because the funerary rites have not completely been performed, or because they have failed; their spirit has not left their body]</font>. <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LXXIX</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
